WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.160
[Amit Varma]: The most useful piece of advice I have ever received was a two-word aphorism.

00:00:09.160 --> 00:00:14.240
[Amit Varma]: Question everything. Do not take received wisdom for granted. Do not give in to

00:00:14.240 --> 00:00:18.520
[Amit Varma]: easy intuitive answers. Ask if the world really works the way people say it does.

00:00:18.520 --> 00:00:23.080
[Amit Varma]: If there are first principles that you consider non-negotiable, apply those

00:00:23.080 --> 00:00:28.880
[Amit Varma]: first principles to everything. If people say X is a problem, re-examine X and see

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:33.480
[Amit Varma]: if it is really a problem. If people say Y is the best solution to X, re-examine Y.

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:38.200
[Amit Varma]: Maybe you will find that a proposed solution makes a problem worse.

00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:43.360
[Amit Varma]: Re-examine everything. Question everything.

